</p></div>"} Make felt stockings for Santa's goodies to be left in. Stockings have long been made from felt and the variations on designs are endless. It's a great way to use up scrap pieces of felt for the design. Read How to make a Christmas stocking for more details. Make gift packaging from felt. Make a felt gift cover that can be reused for other purposes after gifting, such as holding stationery, covering a book, holding bits and pieces, etc. Make little felt bags to hold items like iPods, candies, and other small gifts. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/35/Make-Felt-Christmas-Goodies-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Felt-Christmas-Goodies-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/35/Make-Felt-Christmas-Goodies-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Felt-Christmas-Goodies-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":319,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":527.1978021978022,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
